reviews.review_text:
Great job by Bruce Barnum! Similar to the show the previous night, there are several great AUD pulls of this show too.  But this crispy pull right here sounds super-sweet to my ears.  Jerry lets loose a few times on the Sugaree, and the Birdsong really gets out there!
Eternal rest to taper Bruce Barnum... and God Bless all who have taped live shows over the years, as well as those who continue to do so~

Can't throw a rock without hitting a A++ AUD Seriously, I was going to try and rate the most recent upgrades from each source and they, almost, all sound so good that I just gave up. I thought at one point that I liked this one more than several others, so here I am.

It can often be quite easy to ignore recommendations for anything coming from 85-86. And its not without reason. Things got real dicey between the summer of 84 until the coma in 86. A whole bunch of seriously not good shows occurred. But there was also significantly more high-end music to be found than most folks, I think, are aware of. It can be limited to a song or two, part of a set, or one set or the other. There are also a handful of shows that are popping from start to finish. 3/28/85 is one. And just to cover my bases, this show has boasted outstanding AUDs, well since 3/26/85. I for one have always loved the mixes that come from the Nak300 source, of which this is the latest. And sweet merciful crap, this AUD is a hot fudge super titties Sunday with ice cream made from dank milk. 

Right out of the gate we get a really strong J Straw, followed by a, not quite elite, but real damn close to elite Sugaree. The Bird Song is as good as almost any from the 80-86 period. Then there is the Let it Grow. You won't find more than a dozen better versions ever.

Even more incredible than the wowzers LIG to close S1 is the, (This can't possibly be from 1985) Help> Slip> Frankins to open S2. If this doesn't melt your socks you doing it wrong. The Estimated> Eyes are mostly standard for the time, but even here there isa peppering of cool stuff to hear. Definitely above average Drums> Space> a nice Miracle, and then a simply miraculous China Doll. We are now at 3 Bonafide, all-time, super versions in Let if Grow, Help> Slip> Franklins (I'm counting this as one obv), and China Doll. As if that wasn't enough, they casually drop what is easily the class of 1985, and maybe the best GDTRFB between 12/31/81 and the coma.

Just to reiterate, I close my eyes and picture the crowd during the end of China Doll and see, a mix of dumbstruck, awestruck, uncontrollably crying, some intense grope filled making out, and the rest in full on celebratory mode. .
